-to-minimum-wage/who-gets-the-minimum-wage\" title=\"Who gets the minimum wage\">National Minimum Wage</a>.</p>\n\n<p>If an internship only involves shadowing an employee, ie no work is carried out by the intern, the employer doesn&rsquo;t have to pay the minimum wage.</p>\n\n<h2>Voluntary workers</h2>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;re not entitled to the minimum wage if both the following apply:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re working for a charity, voluntary organisation, associated fund raising body or a statutory body</li>\n  <li>you don&rsquo;t get paid, except for limited benefits (eg reasonable travel or lunch expenses)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Work experience placements</h2>\n\n<p>Work experience students of compulsory school age, ie under 16, aren&rsquo;t entitled to the <a href=\"/your-right-to-minimum-wage/who-gets-the-minimum-wage\" title=\"Who gets the minimum wage\">minimum wage</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Make a complaint</h2>\n\n<p>To make a complaint or for further advice, contact the Pay and Work Rights helpline.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Pay and Work Rights helpline</strong></p>\n\n<p>0800 917 2368</p>\n</div>\n","alternative_title":""},"updated_at":"2012-11-05T11:04:41+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Recruiting and hiring","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Frecruiting-hiring.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes discrimination law, apprenticeships and using agencies","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Frecruiting-hiring","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/recruiting-hiring"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes pay, contracts and hiring","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people"},